ms%20amid%20rising%20living%20costs.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBasic%20income%20trials%20in%20Canada%20date%20back%20to%20the%201930s%2C%20with%20major%20projects%20in%20Manitoba.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ELike%20the%20US%2C%20current%20pilots%20in%20Canada%20show%20mixed%20results%2C%20causing%20debates%20on%20their%20economic%20impact.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20more%20basic%20income%20pilots%20and%20programs%20launch%20in%20the%20United%20States%2C%20Canada%20is%20following%20suit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERecently%2C%20politicians%20in%20Canada%20have%20considered%20how%20to%20implement%20no-strings-attached%20money%20initiatives%2C%20especially%20as%20many%20citizens%20lost%20jobs%20during%20the%20pandemic%20and%20the%20cost%20of%20living%20has%20increased.%20These%20discussions%20have%20drawn%20on%20studies%20and%20trials%20dating%20back%20nearly%20a%20century.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20dozens%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhich-states-cities-have-guaranteed-basic-income-programs-low-income-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ebasic%20income%20programs%20in%20the%20United%20States%3C%2Fa%3E%20spread%2C%20some%20leading%20policy%20experts%20have%20discussed%20whether%20these%20initiatives%20could%20be%20extended%20to%20a%20universal%20level.%20Other%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcountries-with-universal-basic-income%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ecountries%20with%20basic%20income%3C%2Fa%3E%20programs%20and%20experiments%20include%20Brazil%2C%20China%2C%20Germany%2C%20and%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdvocates%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Funiversal-basic-income-ubi%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Euniversal%20basic%20income%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20which%20offers%20recurring%20cash%20payments%20to%20all%20individuals%20in%20a%20population%2C%20regardless%20of%20their%20socioeconomic%20status%20%E2%80%94%20say%20Canada%20has%20the%20resources%20to%20create%20a%20program%20that%20covers%20every%20citizen.%20While%20universal%20income%20would%20be%20on%20a%20universal%20scale%20across%20a%20population%2C%20basic%20income%20programs%20typically%20target%20lower-income%20or%20vulnerable%20populations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOrganizations%20in%20some%20provinces%20are%20testing%20what%20basic%20income%20could%20look%20like%20on%20a%20local%20level%20through%20guaranteed%20basic%20income%20pilots%20%E2%80%94%20recurring%20cash%20payments%20geared%20toward%20specific%20groups%2C%20like%20vulnerable%20populations.%20While%20many%20Canadian%20politicians%20across%20the%20political%20spectrum%20support%20basic%20income%2C%20some%20argue%20that%20these%20programs%20are%20costly%20to%20the%20local%20economy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESupport%20from%20residents%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20varies.%20About%2060%25%20of%20Canadians%20support%20guaranteed%20basic%20income%2C%20while%2037%25%20support%20universal%20basic%20income%2C%20according%20to%20a%20poll%20published%20in%202022%20by%20the%20market%20research%20firm%20Narrative%20Research.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20be%20sure%2C%20cash%20payments%20can't%20replace%20full-time%20income%20or%20lift%20everyone%20out%20of%20poverty%2C%20but%20it%20can%20give%20many%20lower-income%20residents%20more%20opportunities%20to%20engage%20with%20the%20economy%2C%20said%20Sheila%20Regehr%2C%20a%20founding%20member%20and%20chairperson%20of%20the%20Basic%20Income%20Canada%20Network%2C%20an%20organization%20working%20to%20expand%20basic%20income%20access%20across%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFrom%20a%20fiscally%20conservative%20perspective%2C%20that%20little%20bit%20of%20investment%20could%20save%20a%20ton%20of%20money%20down%20the%20road%20and%20get%20better%20results%20for%20everything%2C%26quot%3B%20Regehr%20told%20Business%20Insider%2C%20referring%20to%20the%20initial%20expense%20and%20potential%20benefits%20of%20basic%20income.%20%26quot%3BThis%20idea%20we%20had%20several%20generations%20ago%20to%20get%20a%20good%20job%2C%20stay%20in%20a%20company%20for%20life%2C%20that%20doesn't%20happen%20anymore.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShortly%20after%20the%20pandemic%20began%2C%20talks%20about%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsam-altman-basic-income-study-results-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eefficacy%20of%20basic%20income%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20Canada%20accelerated.%20In%202020%2C%2050%20senators%20sent%20a%20letter%20to%20Prime%20Minister%20Justin%20Trudeau%2C%20Deputy%20Prime%20Minister%20Chrystia%20Freeland%2C%20and%20Finance%20Minister%20Bill%20Morneau%20commending%20them%20for%20their%20actions%20and%20calling%20for%20a%20minimum%20basic%20income.%20And%20in%20the%20last%20federal%20election%20in%202021%2C%20189%20candidates%20%E2%80%94%20representing%2046%25%20of%20Canada's%20electoral%20districts%20%E2%80%94%20pledged%20to%20support%20basic%20income.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECanada's%20Parliamentary%20Budget%20Officer%20found%20that%20between%202022%20and%202023%2C%20a%20universal%20basic%20income%20would%20cost%20%2487.6%20billion%20but%20would%20cut%20poverty%20by%20at%20least%2040%25%20in%20nearly%20every%20province%3B%20the%20cost%20of%20poverty%20totals%20about%20%2480%20billion%20each%20year%2C%20the%20PBO%20estimates.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20certainly%20have%20the%20capacity%2C%20there%20is%20no%20question%20that%20we%20do%2C%26quot%3B%20Regehr%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202021%2C%20Ontario%20Sen.%20Kim%20Pate%20introduced%20Bill%20S-233%20and%20Winnipeg%20MP%20Leah%20Gazan%20introduced%20Bill%20C-233%2C%20creating%20the%20country's%20first%20national%20framework%20for%20a%20guaranteed%20livable%20basic%20income%20for%20people%20over%20the%20age%20of%2017.%20Both%20bills%20are%20now%20under%20consideration%20in%20the%20Senate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECanada%2C%20which%20has%20an%20Old%20Age%20Security%20pension%2C%20already%20has%20a%20version%20of%20basic%20income%20for%20older%20residents%20called%20the%20Guaranteed%20Income%20Supplement.%20The%20GIS%20is%20a%20monthly%20payment%20distributed%20to%20low-income%20pensioners%20aged%2065%20and%20older.%20The%20maximum%20monthly%20payment%20is%20%241%2C087%20for%20someone%20who%20is%20single%2C%20divorced%2C%20or%20widowed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BGetting%20a%20government%20check%20has%20no%20stigma%20to%20it%20here%3B%20it's%20just%20something%20that%20happens%2C%26quot%3B%20Regehr%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22080721e0-fde0-4ef2-ac38-392b85e01663%5C%22%3ECanada's%20experiments%20with%20basic%20income%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Faustin-guarunteed-basic-income-gbi-ubi-housing-security-homeless-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EBasic%20income%20experiments%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20Canada%20are%20not%20new.%20Talk%20of%20implementing%20a%20basic%20income%20dates%20back%20to%20the%201930s%20in%20Alberta%2C%20though%20the%20first%20major%20experiment%20took%20place%20in%20Manitoba%20starting%20in%201974.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20project%2C%20called%20Mincome%2C%20was%20studied%20after%20completion%2C%20and%20researchers%20found%20that%20participants%20%E2%80%94%20who%20received%20%243%2C800%2C%20%244%2C800%2C%20or%20%245%2C800%20a%20year%20through%201979%20%E2%80%94%20on%20the%20whole%20continued%20to%20work%20and%20had%20higher%20secondary%20school%20graduation%20rates.%20Researchers%20also%20found%20that%20there%20was%20an%208.5%25%20drop%20in%20hospitalizations%20for%20participants%20at%20the%20program's%20completion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFour%20decades%20later%2C%20Ontario%20launched%20one%20of%20the%20biggest%20pilots%20in%20Canadian%20history%2C%20the%20Ontario%20Basic%20Income%20Pilot%20Project.%20The%20pilot%2C%20whose%20participants%20were%20mostly%20employed%20and%20lower-income%2C%20gave%20up%20to%20%2416%2C989%20annually%20for%20single%20participants%20aged%2018%20to%2064%20and%20%2424%2C027%20for%20couples.%20Ontario%20Premier%20Doug%20Ford's%20government%20canceled%20the%20pilot%20just%2010%20months%20after%20payments%20were%20first%20distributed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EReasons%20for%20the%20cancellation%20included%20high%20costs%20and%20indications%20that%20the%20program%20didn't%20help%20people%20contribute%20enough%20to%20the%20economy.%20Still%2C%20interviews%20with%20participants%20after%20the%20pilot%20found%20that%20basic%20income%20helped%20them%20better%20afford%20necessities%20than%20traditional%20welfare%20payments%20and%20assisted%20in%20long-term%20financial%20planning.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%202020%20Canadian%20Centre%20for%20Economic%20Analysis%20study%20determined%20that%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbasic-income-helps-people-get-jobs-earn-higher-pay-gbi-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ebasic%20income%20could%20create%20600%2C000%20jobs%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20contribute%20%2480%20billion%20to%20Canada's%20economy%20in%20five%20years%2C%20potentially%20generating%20%24400%20billion%20in%20additional%20GDP%20during%20that%20period.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2276b66032-fd1d-4350-b19e-3fbe7ee56a7d%5C%22%3ECurrent%20basic%20income%20programs%20in%20Canada%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EVarious%20basic%20income%20and%20cash%20transfer%20pilots%20are%20ongoing%2C%20including%20in%20Newfoundland%20and%20Labrador%20for%20people%20between%20the%20ages%20of%2060%20and%2064.%20Quebec%20has%20a%20basic%20income%20of%20%241%2C309%20monthly%20for%20people%20with%20limited%20income%2C%20according%20to%20Quebec's%20government%20website.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPrince%20Edward%20Island%2C%20which%20recently%20hosted%20a%20conference%20on%20basic%20income%2C%20started%20its%20T-BIG%20pilot%20%E2%80%94%20the%20Targeted%20Basic%20Income%20Guarantee%20%E2%80%94%20in%202021%20for%20over%20600%20people.%20The%20program%20gives%20cash%20to%20participants%20to%20bring%20them%20within%2085%25%20of%20the%20federal%20poverty%20level.%20Meanwhile%2C%20a%20few%20provinces%2C%20including%20Saskatchewan%2C%20have%20debated%20adopting%20a%20sovereign%20wealth%20fund%20that%20pays%20dividends%20similar%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Falaska-permanent-fund-basic-income%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EAlaska%20Permanent%20Fund%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202021%2C%20the%20British%20Columbia%20Basic%20Income%20Panel%20created%2065%20recommendations%20for%20implementing%20targeted%20basic%20income%20programs%20for%20people%20with%20disabilities%2C%20young%20Canadians%20aging%20out%20of%20government%20care%2C%20and%20women%20escaping%20violence.%20However%2C%20the%20panel%20recommended%20overhauling%20certain%20social%20programs%20and%20suggested%20against%20a%20general%20basic%20income.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20have%20concluded%20that%20moving%20to%20a%20system%20around%20a%20basic%20income%20for%20all%20as%20its%20main%20pillar%20is%20not%20the%20most%20just%20policy%20option%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20report%20reads.%20%26quot%3BThe%20needs%20of%20people%20in%20this%20society%20are%20too%20diverse%20to%20be%20effectively%20answered%20simply%20with%20a%20cheque%20from%20the%20government.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20province's%20New%20Leaf%20Experiment%20has%20seen%20promising%20results.%20In%20New%20Leaf's%20first%20rendition%2C%20launched%20in%202018%2C%20which%20gave%20%247%2C500%20total%20upfront%20to%2050%20people%20experiencing%20homelessness%20with%20a%20control%20group%20of%2065%20people%2C%20participants%20did%20not%20increase%20spending%20on%20goods%20like%20drugs%20or%20alcohol%20and%20spent%2099%20fewer%20days%20unhoused%2C%20according%20to%20a%20research%20note%20on%20the%20pilot's%20outcomes.%20The%20pilot%20also%20helped%20participants%20with%20financial%20literacy%20and%20getting%20them%20proper%20IDs%20and%20paperwork.%20Results%20are%20forthcoming%20for%20another%20iteration%2C%20which%20started%20in%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20findings%20are%20that%20they%20work%20more%20hours%2C%20they%20get%20paid%20more%20per%20hour%2C%20and%20a%20lot%20of%20the%20individuals%20we're%20working%20with%20are%20accessing%20training%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Amber%20Dyce%2C%20CEO%20of%20Foundations%20For%20Social%20Change%2C%20a%20charitable%20organization%20that%20runs%20the%20New%20Leaf%20pilot.%20%26quot%3BBy%20getting%20the%20cash%20transfer%2C%20they%20have%20more%20breathing%20room.%20They're%20trying%20to%20empower%20themselves%20to%20become%20more%20financially%20stable%20through%20employment.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcanada-ubi%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1750530585000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F684c729cf748d8c055f3b10f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcanada-ubi%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Canada%20has%20been%20exploring%20basic%20income%20programs%20amid%20rising%20living%20costs%20and%20job%20losses.%20They're%20not%20quite%20UBI%2C%20but%20some%20have%20shown%20promising%20results.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22nsheidlower%40businessinsider.com%20(Noah%20Sheidlower)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A57%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcanada-ubi%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22My%20husband%20has%20an%20identical%20twin.%20I%20can't%20tell%20them%20apart%20over%20the%20phone.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225125%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Father%20is%20carrying%20two%20sons.%20Back%20view%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F681ba2db3fe8d392836534ab%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223417%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20author%20(not%20pictured)%20married%20an%20identical%20twin%20and%20had%20fraternal%20twins.%3Cp%3E3photo%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EI%20never%20believed%20in%20love%20at%20first%20sight%20until%20I%20met%20my%20now-husband.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EI%