ai-Pirattal-snails-photo-credit-Paul-McDonough-min-1665580840-150x146.jpg%20150w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F10%2FCopy-of-Nathai-Pirattal-snails-photo-credit-Paul-McDonough-min-1665580840.jpg%201637w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-299905%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22486%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3ENathai%20Pirattal%20at%20Semma.%20Image%3A%20Paul%20McDonough%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20the%20village%20didn%E2%80%99t%20have%20any%20source%20of%20entertainment%2C%20his%20grandparents%20would%20take%20him%20along%20when%20they%20went%20farming.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Clabel%3EAdvertisement%3C%2Flabel%3E%5Cn%3Cins%20data-ad-slot%3D%5C%224678180483%5C%22%20data-ad-client%3D%5C%22ca-pub-5691287967087057%5C%22%20data-ad-format%3D%5C%22fluid%5C%22%20data-ad-layout%3D%5C%22in-article%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9COur%20grandparents%20would%20take%20us%20foraging%20for%20snails%2C%20hunting%20or%20fishing.%20There%20was%20no%20electricity%2C%20buses%20or%20even%20proper%20roads%20at%20that%20time.%20I%20enjoyed%20doing%20these%20activities.%20My%20grandmother%20would%20then%20come%20home%20and%20cook%20the%20snails%20in%20an%20amazing%20gravy%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20the%2041-year-old%20chef.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20as%20he%20grew%20up%20and%20went%20to%20school%2C%20his%20friends%20would%20make%20fun%20of%20him%20for%20eating%20snails.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CSnail%20was%20considered%20a%20poor%20man%E2%80%99s%20food%2C%20or%20a%20farmer%E2%80%99s%20food.%20So%20we%20would%20hide%20it%20or%20not%20get%20it%20to%20school.%20Once%20we%20went%20to%20culinary%20school%2C%20we%20were%20taught%20about%20escargot%2C%20a%20french%20delicacy.%20I%20was%20pleasantly%20surprised.%20I%20remember%20thinking%2C%20%E2%80%98what%20is%20thought%20of%20as%20a%20poor%20person%E2%80%99s%20food%2C%20is%20a%20delicacy%20in%20France%E2%80%99%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Kumar.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDebating%20over%20what%20to%20put%20on%20Semma%E2%80%99s%20menu%20led%20Roni%20and%20Chintan%20to%20add%20snails%2C%20which%20is%20a%20big%20hit.%20Chef%20Vijaya%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20%E2%80%98Nathai%20Pirattal%E2%80%99%2C%20which%20is%20the%20snail%20%3Cem%3Emasala%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20served%20with%20a%20%3Cem%3Ekal%20%3C%2Fem%3Edosa%20sells%20out%20on%20most%20nights.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERoni%20says%20Semma%20honours%20chef%20Kumar%20and%20his%20heritage.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20wanted%20to%20distinguish%20the%20restaurant%20by%20having%20a%20unique%20voice%20and%20perspective.%20Semma%20mimics%20the%20life%20of%20chef%20Vijay.%20It%20honours%20his%20heritage%20and%20includes%20integral%20moments%20of%20his%20life%E2%80%99s%20journey%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%2039-year-old%20Roni.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EFor%20Kumar%2C%20the%20menu%20is%20derived%20from%20his%20childhood%20memories.%20%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETake%2C%20for%20example%2C%20the%20Mulaikattiya%20Thaniyam%20(sprouted%20moong)%2C%20which%20his%20mother%20would%20make%20when%20he%20came%20home%20from%20school%20as%20a%20snack%2C%20or%20the%20Uzhavar%20Santhai%20Poriyal%2C%20which%20is%20made%20with%20vegetables%20bought%20from%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F293356%2Fhealth-benefits-of-kanji-fermented-rice-water-ancient-south-india-food-science%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efarmer%E2%80%99s%20market%20in%20Tamil%20Nadu%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Even%20the%20Chettinad%20Maan%20(Deer)%20carries%20a%20deeply%20personal%20story%20as%20his%20grandfather%20would%20get%20the%20deer.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22auto%2C%20(max-width%3A%20500px)%20100vw%2C%20500px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F10%2FCopy-of-IMulaikattiya-Thaniyam-sprouted-mung-beans-photo-credit-Paul-McDonough-min-1665580998-500x425.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Mulaikattiya%20Thaniyam%20%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F10%2FCopy-of-IMulaikattiya-Thaniyam-sprouted-mung-beans-photo-credit-Paul-McDonough-min-1665580998-500x425.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F10%2FCopy-of-IMulaikattiya-Thaniyam-sprouted-mung-beans-photo-credit-Paul-McDonough-min-1665580998-300x255.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F10%2FCopy-of-IMulaikattiya-Thaniyam-sprouted-mung-beans-photo-credit-Paul-McDonough-min-1665580998-768x653.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F10%2FCopy-of-IMulaikattiya-Thaniyam-sprouted-mung-beans-photo-credit-Paul-McDonough-min-1665580998-1536x1306.jpg%201536w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F10%2FCopy-of-IMulaikattiya-Thaniyam-sprouted-mung-beans-photo-credit-Paul-McDonough-min-1665580998-150x128.jpg%20150w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F10%2FCopy-of-IMulaikattiya-Thaniyam-sprouted-mung-beans-photo-credit-Paul-McDonough-min-1665580998.jpg%202048w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-299906%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22425%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EMulaikattiya%20Thaniyam%20(sprouted%20moong%20beans).%20Image%3A%20Paul%20McDonough%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20restaurant%20prides%20itself%20on%20its%20authenticity.%20So%20the%20meat%20is%20not%20cooked%20off%20the%20bone%2C%20be%20it%20fish%2C%20chicken%20or%20goat.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThousands%20of%20people%20have%20grown%20up%20in%20villages%20and%20moved%20to%20New%20York%20and%20other%20parts%20of%20the%20world.%20When%20they%20eat%20such%20traditional%20food%2C%20they%20form%20an%20instant%20connection.%20So%20many%20customers%20tell%20me%20that%20these%20dishes%20reminded%20them%20of%20their%20mother%20or%20grandmother%E2%80%99s%20cooking%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Kumar.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20don%E2%80%99t%20serve%20food%20in%20a%20way%20you%20might%20expect%20it%20in%20a%20western%2C%20fine%20dining%20restaurant.%20We%20don%E2%80%99t%20want%20to%20pamper%20the%20American%20palate.%20We%20cook%20meat%20with%20the%20bone%20as%20that%20is%20how%20it%20gets%20the%20real%20flavour%2C%20aroma%20and%20taste.%20We%20don%E2%80%99t%20shy%20away%20from%20spices%20too.%20Do%20Italian%20restaurants%20add%20chilli%20powder%20for%20us%3F%20Then%20why%20should%20we%20modify%20our%20dishes%2C%E2%80%9D%20asserts%20chef%20Vijaya.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJust%20like%20the%20snail%20delicacy%2C%20the%20popularity%20of%20the%20Kudal%20Varuval%20(Goat%20intestines)%20has%20pleasantly%20surprised%20the%20chef.%20Most%20big%20restaurants%20in%20cities%20in%20Tamil%20Nadu%20itself%20don%E2%80%99t%20serve%20intestines%2C%20says%20chef%20Vijaya%2C%20which%20he%20recalls%20was%20given%20away%20free%20at%20the%20butcher%20shop%20in%20his%20hometown.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EGoing%20beyond%20Chicken%20Tikka%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20Semma%20and%20Unapologetic%20Foods%2C%20what%20Roni%20and%20the%20team%20aim%20for%20is%20to%20share%20their%20stories.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThere%E2%80%99s%20a%20big%20barrier%20and%20preconceived%20notion%20about%20how%20we%20look%20at%20food.%20We%20only%20look%20at%20it%20through%20the%20lens%20of%20economics.%20In%20this%20process%2C%20we%20eliminated%20certain%20foods%20from%20our%20conversation.%20We%20believe%20that%20flavour%20should%20not%20be%20bound%20by%20economics.%20We%20will%20not%20hold%20back%2C%20our%20food%20will%20have%20real%20spices.%20We%20will%20not%20serve%20boneless%20and%20fillet%20versions%20of%20our%20dishes.%20By%20doing%20that%2C%20you%20are%20eliminating%20the%20real%20cultural%20context%20of%20the%20dish%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Roni.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22auto%2C%20(max-width%3A%20500px)%20100vw%2C%20500px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F10%2Fezgif-5-214f0439b2-min-1665581139-500x443.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Chettinad%20Maan%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F10%2Fezgif-5-214f0439b2-min-1665581139-500x443.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F10%2Fezgif-5-214f0439b2-min-1665581139-300x266.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F10%2Fezgif-5-214f0439b2-min-1665581139-768x680.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F10%2Fezgif-5-214f0439b2-min-1665581139-1536x1360.jpg%201536w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F10%2Fezgif-5-214f0439b2-min-1665581139-150x133.jpg%20150w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F10%2Fezgif-5-214f0439b2-min-1665581139.jpg%201618w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-299908%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22443%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EChettinad%20Maan%20(Deer)%20at%20Semma.%20Image%3A%20Paul%20McDonough%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChef%20Vijaya%20never%20saw%20a%20true%20representation%20of%20the%20food%20he%20grew%20up%20eating%20as%20most%20menus%20in%20the%20US%20served%20chicken%20tikka%20masala%2C%20butter%20chicken%2C%20dal%20and%20saag%20paneer.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CEach%20state%20and%20region%20has%20unique%20flavours%20and%20dishes.%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F270216%2Fmeendum-manjapai-tamil-nadu-ias-supriya-sahu-revives-eco-friendly-cloth-bag%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EIn%20Tamil%20Nadu%20itself%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20there%20are%20so%20many%20micro%20cuisines%2C%20so%20different%20from%20each%20other.%20There%E2%80%99s%20Kongu%20food%20in%20Coimbatore%2C%20and%20different%20flavours%20in%20Madurai%2C%20Chettinad%2C%20etc.%20You%20can%E2%80%99t%20just%20make%20saag%20paneer%20and%20tell%20the%20western%20world%20that%20this%20is%20Indian%20food.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20ingredients%20are%20also%20authentic%2C%20and%20there%20is%20no%20%E2%80%98middle%20ground%E2%80%99%20to%20appease%20everyone%2C%20says%20Roni.%20South%20Indian%20food%20is%20much%20more%20than%20%3Cem%3Eidli%20%3C%2Fem%3Eand%20%3Cem%3Edosa%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CMost%20restaurants%20try%20to%20find%20a%20middle%20ground.%20There%20is%20always%20a%20samosa%20sold%20in%20a%20South%20Indian%20restaurant%20which%20serves%20%3Cem%3Edosa%3C%2Fem%3E%20or%20%3Cem%3Enaan%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20%3Cem%3Echicken%20tikka%20masala%3C%2Fem%3E.%20Mughlai%2FPunjabi%20food%20is%20being%20sold%20as%20%E2%80%98Indian%20food%E2%80%99.%20But%20we%20are%20so%20much%20more%20than%20that.%20There%20is%20Tamilian%2C%20Bengali%2C%20Gujarati%2C%20Punjabi%2C%20and%20Marathi%20cuisine%2C%20just%20to%20name%20a%20few.%20So%20in%20our%20restaurant%2C%20there%20is%20no%20middle%20ground%2C%20and%20we%E2%80%99re%20proud%20of%20it.%20We%20have%20unshackled%20ourselves%20from%20that%20thinking%2C%E2%80%9D%20Roni%20says%20with%20a%20grin.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETherefore%2C%20there%20is%20no%20basmati%20rice%2C%20samosa%2C%20naan%20or%20chicken%20tikka%20masala%20at%20Semma.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22auto%2C%20(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F10%2FUntitled-design-2022-10-12T185924.978-1665581378.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20team%20behind%20Semma%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F10%2FUntitled-design-2022-10-12T185924.978-1665581378.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F10%2FUntitled-design-2022-10-12T185924.978-1665581378-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F10%2FUntitled-design-2022-10-12T185924.978-1665581378-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F10%2FUntitled-design-2022-10-12T185924.978-1665581378-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F10%2FUntitled-design-2022-10-12T185924.978-1665581378-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-299911%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EThe%20team%20behind%20Semma-%20Chintan%20Pandya%2C%20Vijaya%20Kumar%20and%20Roni%20Mazumdar.%20Image%3A%20Paul%20McDonough%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20dishes%20are%20given%20their%20true%20South%20Indian%20names%20sans%20English%20translations.%20Chef%20Vijaya%20says%20that%20if%20mushrooms%20can%20be%20called%20%3Cem%3Efunghi%20%3C%2Fem%3Ein%20an%20Italian%20restaurant%2C%20why%20should%20%3Cem%3Ekozhi%20%3C%2Fem%3Ebe%20called%20%E2%80%98chicken%E2%80%99%20on%20their%20menu%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20Roni%20credits%20the%20chef%20for%20the%20restaurant%E2%80%99s%20success.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9COne%20of%20the%20reasons%20for%20the%20success%20of%20Semma%20is%20Vijay%E2%80%99s%20vulnerability.%20You%20truly%20get%20the%20chef%E2%80%99s%20perspective%20in%20his%20food.%20He%20has%20bared%20his%20soul.%20It%20is%20because%20he%20has%20owned%20who%20he%20is.%20And%20it%E2%80%99s%20liberating.%20We%20don%E2%80%99t%20have%20to%20fit%20into%20someone%20else%E2%80%99s%20rules%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Roni.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20love%20and%20feedback%20of%20people%20keep%20this%20team%20going.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9COne%20day%2C%20I%20saw%20an%20old%20gentleman%20just%20sitting%20alone%20at%20the%20table.%20I%20asked%20him%20if%20everything%20was%20okay.%20He%20said%20that%20he%20was%20remembering%20his%20grandfather.%20The%20food%20he%20ate%20reminded%20him%20of%20eating%20at%20his%20grandfather%E2%80%99s%20house%2C%20and%20he%20said%20that%20since%20he%20left%20Chennai%20many%20years%20ago%2C%20he%20had%20never%20eaten%20anything%20like%20it.%20People%20have%20shed%20tears%20after%20eating%20the%20food%20as%20they%20remember%20moments%20from%20their%20childhood.%20They%20connect%20with%20us%20on%20a%20human%20level%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Roni.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWhen%20you%20no%20longer%20bend%20to%20someone%20else%E2%80%99s%20rules%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20empowering%20to%20everyone%20around%20you%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EEdited%20by%20Yoshita%20Rao%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%3Cem%3EImages%20by%20Paul%20McDonough%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1750430161000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F10%2FCopy-of-Nathai-Pirattal-snails-photo-credit-Paul-McDonough-min-1665580840.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F%3Fp%3D452925%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Semma%E2%80%99s%20chef%20brings%20childhood%20memories%20and%20bold%20regional%20flavours%20to%20the%20global%20stage%2C%20earning%20one%20of%20the%20highest%20honours%20in%20the%20culinary%20world.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22Sowmya%20Mani%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F452925%2Fchef-vijaya-kumar-james-beard-award-semma%2F%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22PM-Kisan%2020th%20Instalment%3A%20How%20Farmers%20Can%20Register%20%26amp%3B%20Complete%20e-KYC%20to%20Get%20Rs%202%2C000%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EOver%2011%20crore%20farmers%20in%20India%20benefit%20from%20the%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpmkisan.gov.in%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20PM-Kisan%20Samman%20Nidhi%20Yojana%3C%2